B.  In-Country Domestic Consultants 

6.  Three in-country domestic consultants (one per country) will be selected and recruited to 
support the international consultant during TA implementation. They will provide 12 person-
months  of  consulting  services.  Those  who  can  conduct  service  delivery  surveys  will  be 
preferred. Each consultant will 
(i)  receive guidance and direction from the lead consultant;  
(ii)  liaise with the in-country team; 
(iii)  conduct the in-country assessment with help from the in-country team and in 
accordance with the format/protocol provided by the lead consultant; 
(iv)  ensure quality and timeliness of all work conducted under the project; 
(v)  prepare the assessment report and liaise with the in-country team to ensure 
there is consensus on the final product; and 
(vi)  assist the in-country team in preparing the presentation of the results of the 
assessment at the regional seminar. 

C.  Domestic Consultant in Manila 

7.  The domestic consultant will be engaged for 10 months to assist the lead consultant in 
the regional seminar and support the international resource persons. He/she will 

(i)  manage the organization of the regional seminar; 
(ii)  provide the resource persons invited to the regional seminar relevant background 
material and administrative assistance; 
(iii)  organize  the  participation  of  in-country  team  members,  resource  speakers, 
partner organizations, and other relevant stakeholders; 
(iv)  review  presentations,  identify  any  apparent  gaps  or  helpful  linkages  in  the 
presentations,  and  maintain  contact  with  resource  persons  to  brief  them  on 
specific papers and how they fit together; 
(v)  serve as a facilitator in the seminar; 
(vi)  closely coordinate with the lead consultant on the seminar program, publicity, 
and media management; 
(vii)  assist in preparing a short summary report on the seminar to serve as the 
Introduction to the seminar proceedings; and  
(viii)  obtain approval from selected presenters to publish their papers.
